cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and specifically part-of-speech tagging.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper evaluates several domain adaptation methods for improving the performance of part-of-speech tagging.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possibility as the paper deals with processing historical texts, which may be of interest to researchers in the field of information retrieval.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possibility as the paper deals with applying machine learning techniques to improve the performance of natural language processing tools.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but the paper may be of interest to researchers studying the impact of technology on language and culture.
